title._content: Campsite at Hawaiian Islands National Wildlife Refuge, June 16, 1962

description._content: Creator: David B. Marshall Local number: SIA2011-1437 Summary: Campsite of refuge inspection team at Hawaiian Islands National Wildlife Refuge, June 16, 1962, Pacific Ocean Biological Survey Program. The caption on the back of this photograph reads, "The Laysan ducks showed no fear and were regular visitors about the tent...attracted by the pan of fresh water." Dates: 1962 Collection: RU 000245 National Museum of Natural History (U.S.) Pacific Ocean Biological Survey Program, Records, circa 1961-1973, with data from 1923. Box 230, Folder 4. Repository: Smithsonian Institution Archives Related blog post: Life in the Field: a Reflection on Cataloging Field Notes in the Pacific Ocean Biological Survey Program View more collections from the Smithsonian Institution.
